Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.44,0:09:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.31,0:09:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I like your enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.52,0:09:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you need to make it clearer to the readers.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.65,0:09:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.53,0:09:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll pretend that I never saw this manuscript.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.20,0:09:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.86,0:09:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a little more thought into it and try again.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.45,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring in something interesting next time.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.70,0:09:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Th—Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.87,0:09:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,D—Did you hear that just now?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.96,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here for the same reason we are, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.67,0:09:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.96,0:09:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pretty confident up till now,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.88,0:09:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but I suddenly think he'll say it's terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.55,0:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be scarier if they {\i1}liked{\i0} the \Nfirst manuscript we brought in.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.76,0:09:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle said it's a good sign \Nif they at least offer us tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.19,0:09:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Takagi and Mashiro?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.06,0:09:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Hattori, an editor for Shounen Jack.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.78,0:09:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you too!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.82,0:10:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not waste time, so can I see the manuscript?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.32,0:10:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.54,0:10:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.29,0:10:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys don't have to be so nervous.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.75,0:10:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yes sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.80,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,F—Finally—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.18,0:10:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's such a fast reader!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.95,0:10:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me read it again.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.53,0:10:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.80,0:11:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Two Earths."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.47,0:11:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth we live on is not the Real Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.39,0:11:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it is no more than a model for experimentation.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.31,0:11:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,created by {\i1}them{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.19,0:11:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato set foot on his home \Nsoil for the first time in a while,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.12,0:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,after being sent back to recover from a war injury.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.95,0:11:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But only a cruel reality awaited \Nhim: the death of his lover, Amy.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.96,0:11:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.66,0:11:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a grip, Hayato! She's dead!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.63,0:11:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw her! She was right over there!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.84,0:11:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.84,0:11:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.51,0:11:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When the light enveloping his body \Ndisappeared, he was in a place he didn't recognize.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.44,0:11:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am— What hap—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.02,0:11:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.85,0:11:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Amy!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.52,0:11:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you running away?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.90,0:12:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, the Other Hayato.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.91,0:12:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the other?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.87,0:12:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? Where am I?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.62,0:12:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on Earth. Well, the Real Earth—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.33,0:12:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth where you Clones live \Nis a test model for the Real Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.22,0:12:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where we, the Real Earthlings, \Nsimulate various scenarios.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.51,0:12:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.56,0:12:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In getting closer to the truth, Hayato became captive.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.94,0:12:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A resistance group known as "Missing" saved him.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.16,0:12:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You too?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.61,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're from the Other Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.24,0:12:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They capture us Clones when they \Nwant to send Investigators in.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.87,0:12:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when the Investigators are done, \Nthey wipe our memories and send us back.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.91,0:13:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the Investigators are killed, we \Nhave no way back, so we have to live here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.38,0:13:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in this shitty utopia.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.14,0:13:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's your way back!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.22,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato returned to Earth and \Ntold his people the situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.81,0:13:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to make them see: we're \Nnot just dolls for them to play with!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.15,0:13:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Other Earth began its counterattack.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.70,0:13:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now. You really think you can shoot me?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.37,0:13:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm your Original, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.58,0:13:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not just your guinea pigs!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.91,0:13:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Die!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.42,0:13:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys really are just animals.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.09,0:13:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Real Earthlings surrendered.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.89,0:13:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But after years of observation, \Nthey had come to a conclusion:
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.56,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That the Other Earthlings were \Nmerely foolish barbarians.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.86,0:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, it's over—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.23,0:14:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all over—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.95,0:14:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're no longer here—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.74,0:14:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't forgive you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.66,0:14:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm your Amy!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.04,0:14:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The dead Amy was an Investigator!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.79,0:14:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If an Investigator dies, the Clone can't come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.38,0:14:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you showed yourself to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.13,0:14:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Original let me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.06,0:14:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a kind man.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.22,0:14:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But the one I loved was always you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.43,0:14:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I've missed you so much, Hayato!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.81,0:14:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As he felt his love close to \Nhim, Hayato rethought his hate.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.15,0:14:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Real and Fake.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.94,0:14:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Real Earth and the Other Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.11,0:14:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one was the actual reality?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.62,0:14:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very well-done.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.37,0:15:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna have some coffee. \NWould you two like anything?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.46,0:15:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,W—We'll have coffee too, please. Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.59,0:15:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.34,0:15:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, did you two come up with the story together?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.01,0:15:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,N—No. I did the story and Mashiro did \Nthe illustrations, completely separate.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.06,0:15:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.52,0:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you two hoping to go pro immediately?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.15,0:15:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! As quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.15,0:15:27.90,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Just "Yes" would've been enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.49,0:15:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay then, I'll start with feedback on the story.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.61,0:15:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.53,0:15:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In general, you have a pretty good sci-fi story.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.45,0:15:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there are definitely people who'd enjoy it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.70,0:15:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.00,0:15:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it's more suited \Nto be a novel than a manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.25,0:15:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's excess narration, and a \Nlot of explanation in the dialogue.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.13,0:15:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't use the characters and illustrations \Nto tell the story, making it a manga is pointless.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.14,0:15:59.60,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,We agreed that I wouldn't say a word about the story,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.60,0:16:01.64,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,but I kind of thought that as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.39,0:16:05.61,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Of course, an editor would say as much though.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.11,0:16:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The story really is well-done though.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.40,0:16:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But it really seems more suited to be a light novel.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.53,0:16:12.82,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are all kinds of editors.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.99,0:16:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I really want to write manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.11,0:16:16.41,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is Mr. Hattori someone we can trust?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.49,0:16:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.33,0:16:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're Mashiro, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.04,0:16:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.09,0:16:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think your art is incredible.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.12,0:16:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.54,0:16:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But while they're incredible works of \Nart, they're not manga illustrations.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.59,0:16:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lines are too thick.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.21,0:16:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not enough differentiation \Nbetween characters and background.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.18,0:16:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to practice more and form your own style.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.52,0:16:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.18,0:16:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.60,0:16:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro's only been using the pen two months.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.61,0:16:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two months? Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.65,0:16:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Y—Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.11,0:16:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true, I can't wait to see \Nwhat he produces in the future.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.07,0:16:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you two like this kind of story?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.70,0:17:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack never has this kind of story.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.83,0:17:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought it'd stand out.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.62,0:17:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Takagi, you're the type who figures out what's \Npopular and what'll sell before writing, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.17,0:17:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the conclusion I've come to,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.13,0:17:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but in general, there's two main \Ntypes of successful mangakas.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.18,0:17:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are those who just write \Nwhatever they want and it becomes a hit.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.98,0:17:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people call them geniuses.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.64,0:17:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Others just call them naive.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.06,0:17:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are those like you, who \Ncalculate how best to create a hit.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.61,0:17:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But overwhelmingly, it's not the \Ncalculating ones who make it big.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.37,0:17:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,W—Well, maybe that was a little harsh.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.20,0:17:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more appropriate to say the calculating \Nones have more hurdles to overcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.50,0:17:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, the calculating \Nones who make it, are tough.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.50,0:17:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't fizzle after one \Nseries, which is great for us editors.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.68,0:18:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I can't force you, but I hope you'll bring\N your next manuscript to us, not another publisher.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.68,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could, I'd like to keep \Nseeing your future works.
